./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:21:[INFO] prd/tech-design.md:25: On fcntl platforms, acquire() ignores an existing lock file containing a live PID unless another process currently holds a flock on the same inode. That contradicts the unchanged tests and existing semantics: test_acquire_already_locked_different_pid_alive writes PID 1 and expects acquire() to return False, but the proposed code would acquire the flock and return True.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:22:[INFO] prd/tech-design.md:55: release() unlinks the lock path even when this FileLockManager never acquired that project. Existing release() is a no-op for locks held by another PID; the proposed version can remove another process's lock file, and with flock this is dangerous because the lock remains on the unlinked inode while a new process can create and lock a new file at the same path.
